                #fillerPane(data-dojo-type="dijit/layout/ContentPane", title="Mash-over Instructions")
                    h3 Using Mash-over
                      
                    p.                              
                        Mash-overs allow viewing mulitple synchronized maps in separate windows.  The maps can use different base maps or different themes for overlays.  Unlike standard layer overlays in a single viewer, the base layers and overlays do not interfere with the visibility or legibility of other selected layers.
                    
                    p.
                        Mash-overs can be created from three map viewer sources, if the viewer incorporates the mash-over component.
                    br
                    ul
                        li 1 An ArcGIS webmap viewer(such as this viewer)<br>
                        li 2 A web page with a google map display<br>
                        li 3 A web page with an open source map display<br>
                    
                    h3 Steps:
                        
                    ul
                        li 1 Open the accordian pane for group search.  Enter a search term and click the submit button.<br>
                        li 2 The group pane displays groups matching the search term.  Click on one of the groups.<br>
                        li 3 The map selection pane opens.  Clicking on a map item opens the WebMap in the default ArcGISOnline WebMap viewer in a new tab.
                        li 4 Drag the tab to the desktop, which displays the tab's contents in a new browser instance.
                        li 5  The two map viewer displays (or any number of generated viewers) are synchronized so that panning or zooming in any map viewer pans or zooms all other map viewers to the same extent.
                    br

